1
00:00:14,360 --> 00:00:17,440
♪In the airport lounge
at the break of day♪

2
00:00:18,040 --> 00:00:22,240
♪A page of dust beneath my fingers♪

3
00:00:22,560 --> 00:00:25,160
♪Filled with stories♪

4
00:00:25,160 --> 00:00:28,280
♪That others never got to tell♪

5
00:00:30,000 --> 00:00:32,960
♪We stand where the law draws its line♪

6
00:00:33,040 --> 00:00:35,600
♪One foot in homeland,
one foot in another land♪

7
00:00:35,680 --> 00:00:37,160
♪With every single stamp we bring down♪

8
00:00:37,200 --> 00:00:40,040
♪The world is split an inch wider♪

9
00:00:40,080 --> 00:00:42,600
♪Raise your eyes, face the light♪

10
00:00:42,760 --> 00:00:45,080
♪See the truth, and see the fright♪

11
00:00:45,280 --> 00:00:46,800
♪Guard the crack within this door♪

12
00:00:46,840 --> 00:00:52,600
♪Keep the way back home
always burning bright♪

13
00:00:54,520 --> 00:00:57,040
♪The camera pans
across the boarding crowd♪

14
00:00:57,080 --> 00:00:59,200
♪Some wear a smile,
some have their eyes adrift♪

15
00:00:59,280 --> 00:01:01,440
♪A red suitcase♪

16
00:01:01,440 --> 00:01:05,360
♪Tied with faded pasts
and broken prayers♪

17
00:01:06,720 --> 00:01:09,400
♪We stand where the law draws its line♪

18
00:01:09,480 --> 00:01:12,080
♪One foot in homeland,
one foot in another land♪

19
00:01:12,160 --> 00:01:13,960
♪With every single stamp we bring down♪

20
00:01:14,040 --> 00:01:17,400
♪It's the heartbeat
echoing the call of law♪

21
00:01:26,000 --> 00:01:30,000
[Gimlet Eyes]

22
00:01:30,000 --> 00:01:33,000
[Episode 21]

23
00:01:34,590 --> 00:01:37,930
You're that sure
it was that old dog?

24
00:01:49,480 --> 00:01:50,490
That doll again.

25
00:01:51,200 --> 00:01:52,850
He really has no new tricks.

26
00:01:55,480 --> 00:01:57,180
The doll is his way
of getting back at me.

27
00:01:57,680 --> 00:01:59,930
I had Shen Taotao arrested,

28
00:02:00,590 --> 00:02:02,330
so he left the doll

29
00:02:03,070 --> 00:02:04,930
and let Customs follow the trail

30
00:02:05,280 --> 00:02:06,410
and find Xiao Dabao.

31
00:02:07,040 --> 00:02:08,410
No wonder you hate him this much.

32
00:02:09,080 --> 00:02:10,410
Exactly. Even if I had to run,

33
00:02:11,000 --> 00:02:12,980
I'd drag him down with me.

34
00:02:14,190 --> 00:02:15,570
But why did you come to me?

35
00:02:17,470 --> 00:02:19,410
You said you're close to finding him.

36
00:02:19,430 --> 00:02:20,610
Are you sure?

37
00:02:21,280 --> 00:02:22,060
No.

38
00:02:23,590 --> 00:02:25,060
That old dog is very cautious.

39
00:02:25,840 --> 00:02:26,980
But I feel like it's him.

40
00:02:27,240 --> 00:02:28,340
If you've heard his voice before,

41
00:02:29,000 --> 00:02:30,290
I'll call him now.

42
00:02:31,080 --> 00:02:32,540
Do you think you can recognize it?

43
00:02:33,080 --> 00:02:33,890
No doubt.

44
00:02:42,680 --> 00:02:43,340
[Mr. E]
Du Li.

45
00:02:43,340 --> 00:02:43,960
[Mr. E]

46
00:02:43,960 --> 00:02:45,660
You finally decided to call me.

47
00:02:46,080 --> 00:02:47,780
What, you want to meet in person?

48
00:02:49,470 --> 00:02:50,260
Hello.

49
00:02:51,800 --> 00:02:52,940
You were looking for me?

50
00:02:52,960 --> 00:02:53,940
Mr. Xiang?

51
00:02:54,870 --> 00:02:55,660
That's me.

52
00:02:56,630 --> 00:02:57,610
Have we met?

53
00:03:00,400 --> 00:03:01,940
Did you place that doll?

54
00:03:02,560 --> 00:03:03,410
Yeah.

55
00:03:05,000 --> 00:03:06,260
But I didn't expect Customs

56
00:03:06,870 --> 00:03:08,940
to be this sophisticated.

57
00:03:09,080 --> 00:03:10,290
They actually went ahead

58
00:03:10,590 --> 00:03:11,220
and released it.

59
00:03:12,150 --> 00:03:13,380
Why did you do this to me?

60
00:03:14,240 --> 00:03:15,060
Why?

61
00:03:15,870 --> 00:03:16,660
Du Li,

62
00:03:17,910 --> 00:03:18,290
do you know

63
00:03:18,310 --> 00:03:21,100
why I told you not to touch Shen Taotao?

64
00:03:21,430 --> 00:03:21,940
Why?

65
00:03:23,000 --> 00:03:26,010
Because she's Guo Cong's girlfriend.

66
00:03:26,280 --> 00:03:27,690
Once she got caught,

67
00:03:27,710 --> 00:03:29,450
you think Guo Cong
would just let you walk?

68
00:03:30,910 --> 00:03:32,820
Then why didn't you
spell it out back then?

69
00:03:33,000 --> 00:03:34,540
Wasn't I clear enough?

70
00:03:35,590 --> 00:03:38,340
I told you, don't let her move goods

71
00:03:38,590 --> 00:03:39,780
ever again.

72
00:03:40,560 --> 00:03:41,610
You didn't listen.

73
00:03:42,000 --> 00:03:43,820
You insisted on going against me.

74
00:03:44,680 --> 00:03:47,130
So this is how you pay me back?

75
00:03:49,560 --> 00:03:50,660
Why would I keep

76
00:03:50,680 --> 00:03:52,010
a pet that won't listen?

77
00:03:53,080 --> 00:03:53,820
For the past three years,

78
00:03:53,840 --> 00:03:55,220
I've always listened to you.

79
00:03:55,240 --> 00:03:57,060
But you kept things from me.

80
00:03:57,710 --> 00:03:58,980
You didn't even tell me

81
00:03:59,000 --> 00:03:59,940
about Long Shuo.

82
00:03:59,960 --> 00:04:00,730
Thanks to that, I lost Ken

83
00:04:00,750 --> 00:04:01,850
and a ton of money.

84
00:04:03,470 --> 00:04:05,100
Well then, my apologies.

85
00:04:05,520 --> 00:04:06,570
Sincerely.

86
00:04:10,870 --> 00:04:11,380
It's him.

87
00:04:11,870 --> 00:04:12,610
Xiang Xiuyuan.

88
00:04:13,190 --> 00:04:14,010
He runs a company

89
00:04:14,590 --> 00:04:15,450
called Xiangliang Trading

90
00:04:16,000 --> 00:04:16,850
at the old shipyard.

91
00:04:18,000 --> 00:04:19,430
[Mr. E, Unmute]

92
00:04:19,430 --> 00:04:20,660
You could say I've been helping you.

93
00:04:21,680 --> 00:04:23,410
Your people failed,

94
00:04:23,600 --> 00:04:25,540
and I cleaned it up for you.

95
00:04:26,160 --> 00:04:27,540
Instead of appreciating that,

96
00:04:27,560 --> 00:04:29,370
you turn around and bite me?

97
00:04:29,630 --> 00:04:30,780
Cut the crap!

98
00:04:30,920 --> 00:04:33,140
So why are you calling me now?

99
00:04:33,430 --> 00:04:34,540
Still want to meet?

100
00:04:34,920 --> 00:04:36,050
Of course I do.

101
00:04:36,720 --> 00:04:38,900
I know you were Sa Ziyi's mule scout.

102
00:04:39,040 --> 00:04:40,170
And I know

103
00:04:40,190 --> 00:04:41,610
you run a major trading firm.

104
00:04:42,480 --> 00:04:44,540
Right now,
you're getting me out of Binhai.

105
00:04:49,310 --> 00:04:51,290
Why should I help you?

106
00:04:52,870 --> 00:04:55,780
Because I've got recordings
of our calls.

107
00:04:56,510 --> 00:04:58,050
So what if you've stayed hidden well?

108
00:04:58,750 --> 00:05:00,250
If I get caught,

109
00:05:00,430 --> 00:05:02,460
those recordings go straight to Customs.

110
00:05:03,080 --> 00:05:05,410
And once that happens, you're next.

111
00:05:08,310 --> 00:05:09,100
Truth is,

112
00:05:09,760 --> 00:05:11,540
even without the recordings,

113
00:05:11,960 --> 00:05:13,340
I'd still help you.

114
00:05:14,280 --> 00:05:16,140
We've worked together for three years.

115
00:05:16,200 --> 00:05:17,980
It's been a good run.

116
00:05:18,950 --> 00:05:20,850
If you ever come back to Binhai,

117
00:05:20,870 --> 00:05:23,290
I think we could still work together.

118
00:05:23,310 --> 00:05:24,780
Come back to Binhai?

119
00:05:24,840 --> 00:05:26,170
I can't even get back
into China anymore!

120
00:05:27,390 --> 00:05:28,900
Then tell me where you are.

121
00:05:29,760 --> 00:05:30,660
I'll come to you.

122
00:05:34,160 --> 00:05:35,020
I'll send you the location.

123
00:05:35,280 --> 00:05:36,220
Come alone.

124
00:05:36,950 --> 00:05:37,730
Relax.

125
00:05:38,510 --> 00:05:40,370
I always work alone.

126
00:05:49,160 --> 00:05:50,020
You're coming with me.

127
00:05:50,310 --> 00:05:50,930
Of course.

128
00:05:51,600 --> 00:05:53,540
I've got a lot to ask him in person.

129
00:06:02,630 --> 00:06:04,730
A trading firm…

130
00:06:28,920 --> 00:06:30,100
After all these years,

131
00:06:31,070 --> 00:06:32,410
you really haven't changed.

132
00:06:35,750 --> 00:06:36,660
Didn't see this coming, did you?

133
00:06:37,870 --> 00:06:39,540
I've been living here for a year.

134
00:07:43,630 --> 00:07:44,050
Dabao.

135
00:07:44,070 --> 00:07:44,460
Li.

136
00:07:45,430 --> 00:07:45,930
You're back.

137
00:07:49,240 --> 00:07:50,660
You're loyal, Xiao Dabao.

138
00:07:51,070 --> 00:07:52,140
Haven't run away even now.

139
00:07:53,920 --> 00:07:55,020
Well, obviously.

140
00:07:57,040 --> 00:07:57,460
Li,

141
00:07:58,750 --> 00:07:59,540
did you find Mr. E?

142
00:08:00,680 --> 00:08:01,250
I did.

143
00:08:02,240 --> 00:08:03,730
I set the meeting here.

144
00:08:04,480 --> 00:08:06,050
About an hour.

145
00:08:06,310 --> 00:08:06,700
Good.

146
00:08:08,120 --> 00:08:08,980
When he shows up,

147
00:08:09,510 --> 00:08:10,980
I'm taking him out.

148
00:08:11,160 --> 00:08:11,930
Dabao,

149
00:08:14,190 --> 00:08:15,220
leave him to me.

150
00:08:17,190 --> 00:08:18,340
Fine, Shuo.

151
00:08:19,800 --> 00:08:21,780
If it really was that old dog

152
00:08:22,190 --> 00:08:23,410
who killed Ziyi,

153
00:08:24,040 --> 00:08:25,700
then you should be the one to finish it.

154
00:08:26,510 --> 00:08:26,900
Right?

155
00:08:30,240 --> 00:08:30,850
Dabao,

156
00:08:31,360 --> 00:08:32,220
put the kettle on.

157
00:08:32,550 --> 00:08:33,010
Got it.

158
00:08:45,510 --> 00:08:46,010
Go have a rest.

159
00:08:53,870 --> 00:08:54,250
Sit here.

160
00:10:06,120 --> 00:10:06,530
Hello?

161
00:10:06,870 --> 00:10:07,340
Hello,

162
00:10:07,400 --> 00:10:08,890
is this Ms. Du?

163
00:10:08,910 --> 00:10:09,700
You have a package.

164
00:10:10,670 --> 00:10:11,460
What?

165
00:10:12,240 --> 00:10:14,060
You've got a package.

166
00:10:14,480 --> 00:10:16,250
Are you in that unfinished building?

167
00:10:17,520 --> 00:10:17,890
Yeah.

168
00:10:17,910 --> 00:10:18,650
Third floor.

169
00:10:18,670 --> 00:10:19,250
Come up.

170
00:10:19,750 --> 00:10:21,610
Is there someone

171
00:10:21,630 --> 00:10:22,820
called Mr. Long?

172
00:10:23,270 --> 00:10:24,460
Mr. Long?

173
00:10:25,630 --> 00:10:26,460
That's me.

174
00:10:33,000 --> 00:10:33,850
Hello, Mr. Long.

175
00:10:34,160 --> 00:10:35,060
Your package.

176
00:10:36,510 --> 00:10:39,010
The delivery note says
it must be handed to you.

177
00:11:58,280 --> 00:12:00,490
Take a look.

178
00:12:32,360 --> 00:12:33,820
You can't catch me.

179
00:12:51,240 --> 00:12:51,850
Li!

180
00:12:54,030 --> 00:12:55,300
Long Shuo, get back here!

181
00:12:56,720 --> 00:12:57,490
Li!

182
00:13:01,150 --> 00:13:03,300
Li, don't fall asleep.

183
00:13:04,030 --> 00:13:06,220
You said you'd go
to Southeast Asia with me!

184
00:13:13,390 --> 00:13:14,180
Li!

185
00:13:29,360 --> 00:13:30,130
Li,

186
00:13:31,200 --> 00:13:32,370
I'll avenge you.

187
00:13:32,670 --> 00:13:33,700
Wait for me.

188
00:13:36,030 --> 00:13:36,820
Xiang Xiuyuan!

189
00:13:39,030 --> 00:13:40,010
Mr. E!

190
00:13:42,270 --> 00:13:43,060
Mr. E!

191
00:13:44,550 --> 00:13:45,490
Mr. Xiang!

192
00:13:47,630 --> 00:13:48,460
Mule scout.

193
00:13:49,790 --> 00:13:51,100
You're just a hound.

194
00:13:52,630 --> 00:13:53,370
A dog.

195
00:13:54,360 --> 00:13:55,700
You're just a pet.

196
00:13:56,870 --> 00:13:58,130
Ziyi said it.

197
00:13:59,480 --> 00:14:00,460
Xiang, you dog!

198
00:14:01,870 --> 00:14:02,650
Come out!

199
00:14:03,720 --> 00:14:04,490
You old dog!

200
00:14:05,790 --> 00:14:06,580
Come out!

201
00:14:08,600 --> 00:14:09,370
Old dog!

202
00:14:29,630 --> 00:14:30,420
Old dog,

203
00:14:32,600 --> 00:14:34,420
how long do you think
you can keep hiding?

204
00:14:37,240 --> 00:14:38,580
Now that I know who you are,

205
00:14:39,270 --> 00:14:41,180
I'll find you.

206
00:14:42,030 --> 00:14:43,180
Don't worry.

207
00:14:43,320 --> 00:14:44,650
I'm not calling the cops.

208
00:14:45,630 --> 00:14:46,890
Only killing you myself

209
00:14:47,510 --> 00:14:48,300
will satisfy me.

210
00:14:50,840 --> 00:14:51,770
Right now,

211
00:14:52,480 --> 00:14:53,490
I've got nothing to lose.

212
00:14:54,480 --> 00:14:55,250
Not like you.

213
00:14:56,600 --> 00:14:57,420
You've got a family

214
00:14:58,270 --> 00:14:58,980
and a business.

215
00:14:59,960 --> 00:15:01,370
You've got everything to lose!

216
00:15:08,840 --> 00:15:09,940
Old dog!

217
00:15:11,960 --> 00:15:13,010
Old dog!

218
00:15:14,790 --> 00:15:15,730
Come out!

219
00:15:20,550 --> 00:15:21,340
Xiang Xiuyuan,

220
00:15:23,120 --> 00:15:24,490
I've killed Du Li.

221
00:15:25,390 --> 00:15:26,700
I'm dead either way.

222
00:15:28,030 --> 00:15:29,820
I don't mind adding a few more bodies.

223
00:15:36,670 --> 00:15:37,460
Old dog,

224
00:15:39,200 --> 00:15:40,010
you won't come out? Fine.

225
00:15:40,270 --> 00:15:42,370
Let's see who outlasts whom.

226
00:15:43,390 --> 00:15:44,370
Old dog!

227
00:15:45,200 --> 00:15:45,890
Come out!

228
00:15:47,120 --> 00:15:47,980
Old dog!

229
00:15:49,150 --> 00:15:49,850
Come out!

230
00:15:51,840 --> 00:15:52,610
Old dog.

231
00:15:54,720 --> 00:15:55,850
Old dog!

232
00:16:04,390 --> 00:16:05,130
Xiang Xiuyuan,

233
00:16:07,030 --> 00:16:08,460
I never thought

234
00:16:09,390 --> 00:16:11,730
you'd be such a coward.

235
00:16:12,550 --> 00:16:15,100
You know what they say:
"You're damned if you do

236
00:16:15,910 --> 00:16:17,610
and damned if you don't."

237
00:16:17,840 --> 00:16:19,220
You really think you can dodge this?

238
00:16:28,840 --> 00:16:31,130
Xiao Dabao,
if you want to avenge Du Li,

239
00:16:31,150 --> 00:16:32,650
come to the old shipyard by the river.

240
00:16:37,720 --> 00:16:39,100
Old dog, I'm in no rush.

241
00:16:40,320 --> 00:16:41,890
Not at all.

242
00:16:43,510 --> 00:16:44,300
Long Shuo.

243
00:16:47,510 --> 00:16:48,940
This is between you and me.

244
00:16:49,480 --> 00:16:50,650
Let's settle it ourselves.

245
00:16:51,600 --> 00:16:52,220
Fine.

246
00:16:53,440 --> 00:16:54,250
Then come out.

247
00:16:54,670 --> 00:16:56,220
We settle it right here.

248
00:17:02,910 --> 00:17:03,490
Alright.

249
00:17:05,240 --> 00:17:06,330
But I know

250
00:17:08,680 --> 00:17:10,660
if I step out now,

251
00:17:11,000 --> 00:17:13,090
maybe I won't get
another chance to talk.

252
00:17:16,240 --> 00:17:18,980
So I need to tell you something first.

253
00:17:19,960 --> 00:17:21,090
I'm sure

254
00:17:21,110 --> 00:17:22,220
you want to hear it, too.

255
00:17:28,350 --> 00:17:29,140
Go on.

256
00:17:29,920 --> 00:17:30,770
I'm listening.

257
00:17:32,510 --> 00:17:33,330
Alright.

258
00:17:39,880 --> 00:17:41,010
I know

259
00:17:41,480 --> 00:17:44,490
you and Sa Ziyi were close.

260
00:17:47,240 --> 00:17:49,940
She brought you up a lot

261
00:17:49,960 --> 00:17:51,220
when she talked to me.

262
00:17:51,640 --> 00:17:54,050
Truth is, I'd been working with her

263
00:17:54,640 --> 00:17:56,490
for over ten years.

264
00:17:57,200 --> 00:17:59,010
I knew her before you did.

265
00:18:00,510 --> 00:18:01,940
And you still did that to her?

266
00:18:06,440 --> 00:18:08,330
Because she wouldn't listen.

267
00:18:08,830 --> 00:18:10,330
She insisted on smuggling drugs.

268
00:18:14,640 --> 00:18:15,810
So you planted the doll.

269
00:18:17,550 --> 00:18:18,530
Yeah.

270
00:18:20,880 --> 00:18:24,420
She wanted to deal drugs.
I wasn't about to go down with her.

271
00:18:24,920 --> 00:18:28,140
She'd seen me. I had to cut ties.

272
00:18:28,160 --> 00:18:30,530
She forced me into it.

273
00:18:32,510 --> 00:18:33,700
But Ziyi told me

274
00:18:34,550 --> 00:18:36,290
you only handled recruiting mules.

275
00:18:36,960 --> 00:18:38,180
You never touched operations.

276
00:18:39,160 --> 00:18:41,050
So how did you know all our plans?

277
00:18:41,960 --> 00:18:43,180
Who's feeding you information?

278
00:18:45,510 --> 00:18:46,140
Long Shuo,

279
00:18:49,160 --> 00:18:50,250
do you remember

280
00:18:50,270 --> 00:18:53,140
that photo in Sa Ziyi's office?

281
00:18:58,310 --> 00:18:59,090
Who took this?

282
00:19:01,880 --> 00:19:03,090
A photographer friend.

283
00:19:04,310 --> 00:19:05,180
How come I've never heard of him?

284
00:19:06,680 --> 00:19:09,010
You get jealous so easily.

285
00:19:10,160 --> 00:19:11,380
I'll introduce you next time.

286
00:19:22,720 --> 00:19:24,880
[Lari, 5 July, Long Shuo]

287
00:19:30,270 --> 00:19:32,180
Go on! Keep talking!

288
00:19:33,880 --> 00:19:34,940
There was another doll.

289
00:19:36,160 --> 00:19:37,330
The day Chen Sanhe died,

290
00:19:38,480 --> 00:19:39,250
you planted it, too.

291
00:19:40,160 --> 00:19:42,180
Those three dolls I placed

292
00:19:43,110 --> 00:19:45,700
were meant to warn Sa Ziyi

293
00:19:46,680 --> 00:19:48,330
and give her a chance to stop

294
00:19:48,350 --> 00:19:50,250
before it was too late.

295
00:19:52,270 --> 00:19:53,530
But I didn't expect

296
00:19:54,160 --> 00:19:55,490
she'd be

297
00:19:55,920 --> 00:19:57,140
that stubborn.

298
00:20:00,000 --> 00:20:01,090
After that,

299
00:20:02,720 --> 00:20:05,810
you didn't just go
after the head of Passenger Inspection.

300
00:20:06,480 --> 00:20:09,250
You even tried to use kids
to smuggle drugs.

301
00:20:14,720 --> 00:20:15,700
That's what they say:

302
00:20:16,070 --> 00:20:19,180
"What goes around comes around."

303
00:20:19,750 --> 00:20:22,250
She brought it on herself!

304
00:20:22,480 --> 00:20:24,050
Sa Ziyi had it coming!

305
00:20:24,070 --> 00:20:25,050
She got what she deserved!

306
00:20:25,240 --> 00:20:26,810
Screw you!

307
00:20:27,240 --> 00:20:28,220
Xiang Xiuyuan!

308
00:20:28,400 --> 00:20:29,460
Get out of here!

309
00:20:30,070 --> 00:20:31,050
Come out!

310
00:20:31,510 --> 00:20:32,860
Come out!

311
00:20:43,920 --> 00:20:44,530
Hit him.

312
00:20:47,510 --> 00:20:48,660
Kill him if you can.

313
00:20:49,550 --> 00:20:50,220
Xiao Dabao.

314
00:20:53,160 --> 00:20:53,770
I told you

315
00:20:54,550 --> 00:20:55,460
I didn't want to fight you.

316
00:21:00,200 --> 00:21:01,330
You killed Li.

317
00:21:02,310 --> 00:21:03,940
I'm killing you!

318
00:21:21,480 --> 00:21:22,250
Xiao Dabao,

319
00:21:22,960 --> 00:21:24,980
I respect you. You're a stand-up guy.
Loyal and true.

320
00:21:25,310 --> 00:21:26,420
But you left me no choice.

321
00:25:06,830 --> 00:25:09,010
You think I'm not tired enough already?

322
00:25:09,720 --> 00:25:10,490
Wouldn't it

323
00:25:11,110 --> 00:25:12,700
be better if you just lived
your damn lives?

324
00:25:12,790 --> 00:25:14,420
Why did you want me dead so badly?

325
00:25:14,680 --> 00:25:16,810
What can you even get from that?

326
00:25:17,030 --> 00:25:18,180
Now you're the dead ones!

327
00:25:19,440 --> 00:25:21,420
You turned yourselves into animals.

328
00:25:21,830 --> 00:25:24,250
Why turn me into one, too?

329
00:25:24,270 --> 00:25:28,460
Why force me to become a killer, too?

330
00:25:29,030 --> 00:25:30,010
Why?

331
00:25:30,270 --> 00:25:31,140
I'm

332
00:25:31,880 --> 00:25:32,770
a decent man.

333
00:25:32,830 --> 00:25:34,460
A man with principles!

334
00:25:34,480 --> 00:25:36,090
If you'd just played by my rules,

335
00:25:36,920 --> 00:25:38,660
you'd all still be alive.

336
00:25:38,680 --> 00:25:39,770
Du Li would be alive.

337
00:25:39,790 --> 00:25:41,220
Sa Ziyi would be alive.

338
00:25:41,510 --> 00:25:43,050
Why were you trying to kill me?

339
00:25:43,240 --> 00:25:44,730
Why?

340
00:25:45,070 --> 00:25:46,140
Why?

341
00:25:46,920 --> 00:25:49,620
You kept leaving mess after mess for me,
making me clean it up.

342
00:25:49,640 --> 00:25:51,180
You think this is funny?

343
00:25:51,200 --> 00:25:52,900
You sleep well down there?

344
00:25:54,720 --> 00:25:55,860
Now you're all dead.

345
00:25:55,920 --> 00:25:58,250
You thought you'd die
nice and easy, huh?

346
00:25:59,440 --> 00:26:00,460
Get up.

347
00:26:01,030 --> 00:26:02,050
Get up!

348
00:26:02,830 --> 00:26:04,220
You too, get up!

349
00:26:04,440 --> 00:26:05,530
Get up!

350
00:26:05,790 --> 00:26:06,860
Get up!

351
00:26:08,030 --> 00:26:09,220
Done playing now?

352
00:26:09,790 --> 00:26:11,420
Can't keep going?

353
00:26:11,480 --> 00:26:12,900
Was all this just to screw me over?

354
00:26:12,920 --> 00:26:13,700
You wanted to mess with me?

355
00:26:14,440 --> 00:26:15,420
Go on!

356
00:26:15,440 --> 00:26:16,810
Weren't you so capable before?

357
00:26:17,200 --> 00:26:19,420
Now you've got no choice
but to play by my rules.

358
00:26:20,270 --> 00:26:21,620
Now be a good boy.

359
00:26:30,310 --> 00:26:31,250
It's fine.

360
00:26:32,680 --> 00:26:33,530
Dust returns

361
00:26:34,480 --> 00:26:35,660
to dust.

362
00:26:36,830 --> 00:26:38,460
What lives must die.

363
00:26:47,160 --> 00:26:51,200
[Binhai Huayan Airport Customs]

364
00:26:51,200 --> 00:26:51,810
Mr. Shen,

365
00:26:52,160 --> 00:26:52,660
any updates?

366
00:26:53,830 --> 00:26:56,220
The operation to take down
Xiao Dabao's ring is still ongoing.

367
00:26:56,270 --> 00:26:57,090
But we didn't expect

368
00:26:57,400 --> 00:26:58,980
this to lead us to Group E as well.

369
00:26:59,590 --> 00:27:00,860
Let me brief everyone.

370
00:27:01,030 --> 00:27:01,330
Alright.

371
00:27:03,270 --> 00:27:04,050
Everyone, take a seat.

372
00:27:04,060 --> 00:27:06,000
[Binhai Huayan Airport Customs]

373
00:27:06,000 --> 00:27:06,530
Mr. Shen.

374
00:27:13,440 --> 00:27:14,180
Here's what we've got.

375
00:27:15,310 --> 00:27:16,900
When we moved in on Xiao Dabao,

376
00:27:16,920 --> 00:27:17,810
he had already fled.

377
00:27:18,480 --> 00:27:19,660
But we got information

378
00:27:19,680 --> 00:27:20,570
from the police.

379
00:27:21,030 --> 00:27:23,380
At the last place he was seen,

380
00:27:23,400 --> 00:27:24,620
they found a victim.

381
00:27:25,000 --> 00:27:26,010
Her name is Du Li.

382
00:27:26,400 --> 00:27:28,770
Based on the investigation
into her residence

383
00:27:28,790 --> 00:27:30,290
and communication records,

384
00:27:30,440 --> 00:27:31,940
Du Li turns out to be

385
00:27:31,960 --> 00:27:33,980
the real head of the smuggling ring.

386
00:27:34,240 --> 00:27:35,620
Xiao Dabao worked for her.

387
00:27:35,680 --> 00:27:37,420
They posed as siblings.

388
00:27:37,830 --> 00:27:38,980
Who killed Du Li?

389
00:27:39,070 --> 00:27:40,250
Possibly Long Shuo.

390
00:27:40,640 --> 00:27:42,420
At the scene, police found photos

391
00:27:42,680 --> 00:27:43,460
of Du Li

392
00:27:43,480 --> 00:27:44,730
poisoning Sa Ziyi

393
00:27:44,880 --> 00:27:47,330
by the seaside three years ago.

394
00:27:48,070 --> 00:27:49,220
The current theory is

395
00:27:49,590 --> 00:27:51,900
Long Shuo saw those photos
and killed her

396
00:27:52,240 --> 00:27:53,090
in a rage.

397
00:27:54,070 --> 00:27:56,090
Where did Long Shuo and Xiao Dabao go?

398
00:27:56,400 --> 00:27:57,570
Police are still tracking them.

399
00:27:57,880 --> 00:27:59,620
Who took those photos?

400
00:27:59,880 --> 00:28:01,460
And how did they end up with Long Shuo?

401
00:28:02,200 --> 00:28:03,380
We don't know yet.

402
00:28:04,070 --> 00:28:05,860
But whoever this person is,
they're deeply hidden.

403
00:28:07,070 --> 00:28:08,010
Best we can tell,

404
00:28:08,030 --> 00:28:10,810
three years ago,

405
00:28:10,830 --> 00:28:14,010
this person likely orchestrated
Du Li's killing of Sa Ziyi.

406
00:28:14,440 --> 00:28:16,010
And now,

407
00:28:16,030 --> 00:28:17,220
they used the evidence

408
00:28:17,510 --> 00:28:18,700
to eliminate Du Li.

409
00:28:19,880 --> 00:28:21,620
Classic murder by proxy.

410
00:28:21,960 --> 00:28:23,180
One blade, two kills.

411
00:28:23,880 --> 00:28:25,380
Maybe more.

412
00:28:27,110 --> 00:28:28,380
At this point, we can basically conclude

413
00:28:28,920 --> 00:28:29,290
this person

414
00:28:29,310 --> 00:28:31,980
is the key link between Sa Ziyi's ring

415
00:28:32,000 --> 00:28:33,490
and Du Li's ring.

416
00:28:33,750 --> 00:28:34,860
And both times,

417
00:28:35,270 --> 00:28:36,180
they managed to get away.

418
00:28:36,400 --> 00:28:38,420
Any other leads on our side?

419
00:28:38,790 --> 00:28:39,570
No.

420
00:28:40,200 --> 00:28:41,220
For now, all we can do

421
00:28:41,240 --> 00:28:44,220
is hope the police catch
Long Shuo and Xiao Dabao soon.

422
00:28:46,440 --> 00:28:48,660
This person is clearly
highly intelligent.

423
00:28:50,070 --> 00:28:51,660
Staying hidden extremely well.

424
00:28:51,830 --> 00:28:53,940
Very skilled at getting away clean.

425
00:28:54,440 --> 00:28:56,660
Treating their partners
like expendable pieces.

426
00:28:56,680 --> 00:28:57,620
Use them and then discard them.

427
00:28:57,640 --> 00:28:58,860
Cold and ruthless.

428
00:28:59,160 --> 00:28:59,940
The way they focus

429
00:28:59,960 --> 00:29:01,980
on recruiting mules

430
00:29:02,000 --> 00:29:02,900
shows

431
00:29:03,510 --> 00:29:05,490
a strong need to control people,

432
00:29:06,720 --> 00:29:08,250
which suggests they may have

433
00:29:08,720 --> 00:29:09,700
antisocial personality traits.

434
00:29:12,310 --> 00:29:12,980
That's everything

435
00:29:13,200 --> 00:29:15,180
we've got so far.

436
00:29:15,720 --> 00:29:16,330
These

437
00:29:16,790 --> 00:29:19,460
were found at Du Li's place.
A whole stack of photos.

438
00:29:20,550 --> 00:29:21,700
[File Box]
Based on our analysis,

439
00:29:21,920 --> 00:29:23,050
[File Box]
this is their pool

440
00:29:23,310 --> 00:29:25,010
of potential mules.

441
00:29:25,830 --> 00:29:26,420
We've already arrested

442
00:29:26,440 --> 00:29:27,980
and dealt with some of these people.

443
00:29:28,000 --> 00:29:28,900
As for the others,

444
00:29:29,400 --> 00:29:30,900
we're still not sure
if they're involved.

445
00:29:30,920 --> 00:29:31,620
Take a good look.

446
00:29:31,830 --> 00:29:32,620
Memorize what you can.

447
00:29:32,880 --> 00:29:34,620
If any of them show up at Customs,

448
00:29:35,110 --> 00:29:35,900
check them carefully.

449
00:29:36,440 --> 00:29:37,090
Got it.

450
00:29:37,590 --> 00:29:37,900
Alright.

451
00:29:38,680 --> 00:29:39,380
Good work, everyone.

452
00:29:40,000 --> 00:29:40,620
Just doing our job.

453
00:29:48,440 --> 00:29:49,660
That's Qian.

454
00:29:49,680 --> 00:29:50,570
"Twenty-one.

455
00:29:50,640 --> 00:29:51,810
Studies in Canada.

456
00:29:51,960 --> 00:29:53,490
Mother works in Customs.

457
00:29:53,830 --> 00:29:55,010
Father runs a business out of town.

458
00:29:55,030 --> 00:29:56,010
Feels insecure.

459
00:29:56,200 --> 00:29:56,980
Craves affection."

460
00:29:59,480 --> 00:30:00,490
"Qian Shengkai.

461
00:30:01,110 --> 00:30:01,770
Thirty-five.

462
00:30:02,110 --> 00:30:02,810
Family man with a daughter.

463
00:30:02,830 --> 00:30:03,810
Electrical engineer.

464
00:30:04,000 --> 00:30:05,010
Lost money in blockchain.

465
00:30:05,030 --> 00:30:06,050
Half a million in debt.

466
00:30:06,270 --> 00:30:07,380
Won't accept a loss."

467
00:30:07,480 --> 00:30:08,420
And Liu Kai.

468
00:30:08,880 --> 00:30:10,380
Look at this list.

469
00:30:12,640 --> 00:30:14,010
This mule scout is so outrageous.

470
00:30:15,160 --> 00:30:16,250
We've seen

471
00:30:16,270 --> 00:30:17,460
a lot of these faces before.

472
00:30:17,790 --> 00:30:18,940
Gotta say though,

473
00:30:19,240 --> 00:30:20,040
whoever took these photos

474
00:30:20,040 --> 00:30:20,860
[Urgent Coordination Notice]
knows what they're doing.

475
00:30:21,550 --> 00:30:22,620
Shame it's used like this.

476
00:30:23,310 --> 00:30:23,770
Look at this one.

477
00:30:28,030 --> 00:30:29,380
Why

478
00:30:29,790 --> 00:30:32,180
does the background

479
00:30:32,350 --> 00:30:34,900
in Qian Shengkai's photo

480
00:30:35,480 --> 00:30:37,090
look like one I've seen before?

481
00:30:38,720 --> 00:30:40,490
Where have you seen it?

482
00:30:44,680 --> 00:30:48,180
I think…
at Mr. Xiang's photography exhibit.

483
00:30:50,880 --> 00:30:51,860
You sure?

484
00:31:31,030 --> 00:31:31,620
Zhang.

485
00:31:32,000 --> 00:31:33,010
Hey, Mr. Xiang.

486
00:31:33,590 --> 00:31:34,330
Are you at the office?

487
00:31:35,070 --> 00:31:36,250
Yeah, I'm here.

488
00:31:36,480 --> 00:31:36,940
What's up?

489
00:31:37,200 --> 00:31:37,620
Okay.

490
00:31:37,640 --> 00:31:39,420
Guo Cong and I are coming by.

491
00:31:39,510 --> 00:31:40,420
Are you busy now?

492
00:31:40,790 --> 00:31:41,380
You're

493
00:31:42,030 --> 00:31:42,700
coming over?

494
00:31:42,790 --> 00:31:43,420
Yeah.

495
00:31:44,590 --> 00:31:45,420
Do you have a second?

496
00:31:45,440 --> 00:31:46,250
Yeah, I'm here.

497
00:31:46,270 --> 00:31:47,050
I'll wait for you.

498
00:31:47,070 --> 00:31:47,620
Come on over.

499
00:31:47,920 --> 00:31:48,290
Alright,

500
00:31:48,440 --> 00:31:49,290
we're heading out.

501
00:32:10,920 --> 00:32:11,980
Still,

502
00:32:13,310 --> 00:32:14,810
we can't just go off one photo

503
00:32:15,400 --> 00:32:16,010
and

504
00:32:16,550 --> 00:32:18,250
say Mr. Xiang is that person.

505
00:32:44,000 --> 00:32:48,440
[Photos and Videos]

506
00:32:48,440 --> 00:32:50,360
[Deng]

507
00:32:55,400 --> 00:32:55,940
Deng,

508
00:32:56,790 --> 00:32:58,050
I've sent you two photos.

509
00:32:58,790 --> 00:32:59,860
Have Qian take a look.

510
00:33:00,200 --> 00:33:01,660
See if she recognizes this person.

511
00:33:02,440 --> 00:33:03,810
Most importantly,

512
00:33:04,310 --> 00:33:05,860
ask her if he ever took her photo.

513
00:33:11,400 --> 00:33:12,180
Right,

514
00:33:12,270 --> 00:33:13,050
Qian.

515
00:33:29,830 --> 00:33:30,660
Mr. Guo,

516
00:33:31,160 --> 00:33:32,290
I've seen him before.

517
00:33:33,550 --> 00:33:34,330
Miss,

518
00:33:36,000 --> 00:33:36,770
I took

519
00:33:37,790 --> 00:33:39,420
a few shots of you just now.

520
00:33:40,160 --> 00:33:41,940
I don't know what you're going through,

521
00:33:42,750 --> 00:33:45,330
but you look really down in them.

522
00:33:47,590 --> 00:33:49,010
That's a pretty high-end camera.

523
00:33:49,960 --> 00:33:51,140
Are you a photographer?

524
00:33:52,590 --> 00:33:53,900
Just a hobby of mine.

525
00:33:57,550 --> 00:33:58,490
Here's my card.

526
00:34:00,920 --> 00:34:02,200
[President,
Binhai Photographers Association]

527
00:34:02,200 --> 00:34:03,730
President
of the Photographers Association?

528
00:34:03,750 --> 00:34:04,940
That's more than just a hobby.

529
00:34:05,310 --> 00:34:07,090
I might include your photos

530
00:34:07,350 --> 00:34:09,210
in my photography exhibition.

531
00:34:10,630 --> 00:34:12,530
I usually check with people first

532
00:34:12,590 --> 00:34:14,090
and make sure they're okay with it.

533
00:34:14,710 --> 00:34:17,690
If you're not, I won't use them.

534
00:34:18,630 --> 00:34:20,420
Suit yourself. I don't care.

535
00:34:22,190 --> 00:34:23,530
You're still young.

536
00:34:23,550 --> 00:34:25,610
You should really pay attention
to your image rights.

537
00:34:26,510 --> 00:34:28,210
Maybe talk it over
with your parents first?

538
00:34:28,230 --> 00:34:29,530
I don't have parents.

539
00:34:29,960 --> 00:34:32,980
I decide things for myself.

540
00:34:36,630 --> 00:34:37,650
All I can say is

541
00:34:37,670 --> 00:34:40,900
every parent has their own struggles.

542
00:34:43,630 --> 00:34:44,980
Is your dad good to you?

543
00:34:45,040 --> 00:34:46,130
My dad?

544
00:34:48,710 --> 00:34:51,050
Feels like he's been missing
my whole life.

545
00:34:51,800 --> 00:34:53,050
As for my mom,

546
00:34:53,320 --> 00:34:54,530
I don't get

547
00:34:54,880 --> 00:34:56,010
how she put up with it.

548
00:34:56,630 --> 00:34:58,740
If it were me,
I'd have left a long time ago.

549
00:34:59,150 --> 00:35:00,610
My son and I get along well.

550
00:35:01,520 --> 00:35:02,650
Not so much with his mom.

551
00:35:02,920 --> 00:35:04,610
Maybe she's too strict with him.

552
00:35:06,710 --> 00:35:08,260
You and your mom must be close, right?

553
00:35:11,800 --> 00:35:13,010
I'm not close to anyone.

554
00:35:14,150 --> 00:35:16,050
To her, I'm just a burden.

555
00:35:16,520 --> 00:35:17,610
But it's fine now.

556
00:35:18,320 --> 00:35:19,860
She sent me off to Canada.

557
00:35:20,110 --> 00:35:21,130
Problem solved.

558
00:35:23,400 --> 00:35:24,530
You've probably got her wrong.

559
00:35:24,920 --> 00:35:26,610
I'm sure she loves you.

560
00:35:26,670 --> 00:35:27,460
No.

561
00:35:27,920 --> 00:35:29,210
She loves her job.

562
00:35:30,550 --> 00:35:31,570
Can I ask

563
00:35:31,590 --> 00:35:33,010
what she does?

564
00:35:33,400 --> 00:35:35,050
Nothing special.

565
00:35:35,960 --> 00:35:36,690
Customs.

566
00:35:37,520 --> 00:35:38,530
Passenger Inspection.

567
00:35:44,360 --> 00:35:45,090
I see.

568
00:35:47,400 --> 00:35:49,490
That job is actually tiresome.

569
00:35:49,960 --> 00:35:51,090
Especially during holidays.

570
00:35:51,400 --> 00:35:54,300
Like now, Christmas season.

571
00:35:55,070 --> 00:35:56,650
There are lots
of inbound and outbound travelers.

572
00:35:57,480 --> 00:35:58,940
You should try to understand her.

573
00:36:00,070 --> 00:36:01,340
Then who's supposed to understand

574
00:36:01,400 --> 00:36:03,300
the kids left on their own?

575
00:36:04,920 --> 00:36:06,650
You said you're 18.

576
00:36:06,670 --> 00:36:07,820
Now you're a kid again?

577
00:36:08,070 --> 00:36:10,940
But I grew up like that.

578
00:36:14,070 --> 00:36:16,090
Guess it's fate we ran into each other.

579
00:36:18,510 --> 00:36:19,170
Here.

580
00:36:22,070 --> 00:36:22,980
Leave me your number

581
00:36:23,040 --> 00:36:24,260
or an address.

582
00:36:24,920 --> 00:36:26,460
If anything comes up,

583
00:36:27,360 --> 00:36:28,460
I'll try to help.

584
00:36:33,480 --> 00:36:34,610
Why would you help me?

585
00:36:37,670 --> 00:36:40,130
Because your mom works at Customs.

586
00:36:40,550 --> 00:36:43,460
That's a job worth respecting.

587
00:36:44,520 --> 00:36:45,900
You'll understand someday.

588
00:36:54,480 --> 00:36:55,610
Maybe that's just

589
00:36:55,630 --> 00:36:56,650
how your generation sees it.

590
00:36:59,030 --> 00:37:01,260
Honestly, every job deserves respect.

591
00:37:01,880 --> 00:37:02,860
Not just hers.

592
00:37:04,400 --> 00:37:05,380
Alright.

593
00:37:07,360 --> 00:37:09,090
You've vented enough.

594
00:37:10,230 --> 00:37:11,690
If there's nothing else, head home.

595
00:37:12,520 --> 00:37:13,260
A cold front's coming.

596
00:37:13,320 --> 00:37:14,050
Dress warm.

597
00:37:14,150 --> 00:37:15,050
Don't catch a cold.

598
00:37:33,040 --> 00:37:34,010
Got it.

599
00:38:02,630 --> 00:38:03,420
That's the one.

600
00:38:37,000 --> 00:38:37,420
Mentor,

601
00:38:37,880 --> 00:38:40,090
we stick to the plan
we talked about in the car.

602
00:38:40,710 --> 00:38:41,050
Alright.

603
00:38:41,480 --> 00:38:41,780
Okay.

604
00:38:46,840 --> 00:38:48,420
We're pretending to be a couple.

605
00:38:48,480 --> 00:38:49,380
Try to look a little happier.

606
00:38:54,620 --> 00:38:59,000
[Vintage, Toys, Goodies]

607
00:39:10,550 --> 00:39:11,490
Mr. Xiang.

608
00:39:11,670 --> 00:39:12,050
Uncle Xiang.

609
00:39:15,480 --> 00:39:17,420
Why are you working on your own?

610
00:39:17,630 --> 00:39:18,780
That's a lot to handle.

611
00:39:19,400 --> 00:39:20,420
The guys went out on a delivery.

612
00:39:21,230 --> 00:39:21,980
I'm just cleaning up a bit.

613
00:39:22,800 --> 00:39:23,780
What happened to your thumb?

614
00:39:25,630 --> 00:39:27,010
I was moving an old cabinet yesterday.

615
00:39:27,400 --> 00:39:28,340
There was a nail sticking out.

616
00:39:28,520 --> 00:39:29,490
I didn't notice and scraped it.

617
00:39:30,070 --> 00:39:30,570
It's nothing.

618
00:39:31,030 --> 00:39:31,650
Be careful.

619
00:39:36,040 --> 00:39:36,980
So what brings you two here?

620
00:39:38,520 --> 00:39:40,380
I've been learning photography
from you, right?

621
00:39:40,800 --> 00:39:41,420
But

622
00:39:41,480 --> 00:39:43,530
Guo Cong saw my shots
and said they were bad.

623
00:39:43,590 --> 00:39:45,460
He said when he was young,
he learned from you, too.

624
00:39:45,630 --> 00:39:46,460
And he said my photos

625
00:39:46,480 --> 00:39:48,340
didn't even measure up to what he took
when he was a teen.

626
00:39:48,880 --> 00:39:50,740
Cong did pick it up fast back then.

627
00:39:51,920 --> 00:39:53,380
If he hadn't gone into Customs,

628
00:39:53,590 --> 00:39:54,780
he might've ended up better than me.

629
00:39:54,800 --> 00:39:55,650
Really?

630
00:39:55,960 --> 00:39:56,860
Then I've gotta see

631
00:39:56,880 --> 00:39:58,380
this prodigy's early work.

632
00:39:58,710 --> 00:40:00,050
I need to learn from it.

633
00:40:02,000 --> 00:40:03,050
I don't remember where I put those.

634
00:40:03,070 --> 00:40:03,690
Let me check.

635
00:40:03,880 --> 00:40:04,690
- Yeah, please.
- I'll go find them for you.

636
00:40:04,710 --> 00:40:05,690
I really want to see.

637
00:40:07,110 --> 00:40:08,090
Take your time.

638
00:40:09,110 --> 00:40:09,980
You're awfully quiet today.

639
00:40:24,400 --> 00:40:25,210
Cong, come here.

640
00:40:29,030 --> 00:40:30,170
You two wait here.

641
00:40:30,440 --> 00:40:31,980
I'll bring the photos down
once I find them.

642
00:40:32,710 --> 00:40:33,130
Alright.

643
00:40:52,880 --> 00:40:54,570
Do you remember
what the photo looked like?

644
00:40:56,190 --> 00:40:58,860
I just remember it was a kid.

645
00:40:59,760 --> 00:41:02,570
The background looked almost the same
as the one with Qian Shengkai.

646
00:41:03,440 --> 00:41:05,940
Probably taken in the same place.

647
00:41:06,230 --> 00:41:07,650
If it was displayed before,

648
00:41:07,670 --> 00:41:08,780
it should've been framed.

649
00:41:23,480 --> 00:41:24,260
This one.

650
00:42:24,670 --> 00:42:25,380
Mentor.

651
00:42:26,230 --> 00:42:27,210
Come take a look.

652
00:42:32,070 --> 00:42:32,610
Same spot

653
00:42:33,320 --> 00:42:34,210
as Qian Shengkai's.

654
00:42:47,590 --> 00:42:48,420
Here, take it.

655
00:42:55,800 --> 00:42:56,420
Qian Shengkai.

656
00:43:30,800 --> 00:43:37,360
♪There's a place of simple,
everyday warmth♪

657
00:43:38,280 --> 00:43:45,000
♪A door left open
for the wandering soul♪

658
00:43:45,920 --> 00:43:52,440
♪A humble table still warm with love♪

659
00:43:52,680 --> 00:43:56,320
♪After you've tasted every high and low♪

660
00:43:56,600 --> 00:44:00,240
♪Come home, I'll keep you warm♪

661
00:44:01,000 --> 00:44:07,680
♪Where the days begin and end♪

662
00:44:08,440 --> 00:44:15,320
♪A light still on for the ones
who've lost their way♪

663
00:44:16,120 --> 00:44:22,680
♪An embrace waiting just for you♪

664
00:44:22,960 --> 00:44:26,680
♪Through every passing season♪

665
00:44:26,800 --> 00:44:30,480
♪Even if you return with nothing at all♪

666
00:44:31,120 --> 00:44:34,600
♪Turn around and look♪

667
00:44:34,800 --> 00:44:38,600
♪That door's still open♪

668
00:44:38,800 --> 00:44:42,440
♪A light still burning♪

669
00:44:42,520 --> 00:44:46,240
♪Waiting there for you♪

670
00:44:46,400 --> 00:44:49,920
♪Turn around and look♪

671
00:44:50,160 --> 00:44:53,960
♪Someone's still waiting♪

672
00:44:54,160 --> 00:44:57,760
♪Watching the dusk settle in♪

673
00:44:57,840 --> 00:45:01,560
♪Waiting for the break of dawn♪

674
00:45:03,320 --> 00:45:07,000
♪It's always there♪
